# system-updater configuration
#
# Format:        key=value (shell-sourced; bash semantics, comments with #).
# Default path:  $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/system-updater/config
#                (typically ~/.config/system-updater/config). Override via
#                --config <path> or the UPDATER_CONFIG_FILE environment
#                variable.
#
# All knobs here are UPDATER_* environment variables. The script applies
# the defaults shown below if a variable is unset.
#
# Defaults are SAFE: dry-run preview, apt backend (auto-detected), no
# holds, no maintenance window, no snapshot requirement, no auto-reboot.
# You only need to set values to opt into stricter behavior.

# ── Log location ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default: $XDG_STATE_HOME/system-updater (~/.local/state/system-updater).
# Holds updater.jsonl, updater-last-run.json, .health-baseline, updater.lock.
#
# UPDATER_LOG_DIR="$HOME/.local/state/system-updater"

# ── Backend ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# One of: apt, stub, auto (default). 'auto' picks apt when apt-get is on
# $PATH, otherwise stub. The stub backend is a no-op used by tests and
# non-apt hosts.
#
# UPDATER_BACKEND=auto

# ── Holds ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Space-separated glob list of package names to NEVER upgrade. Matched
# packages are reported with status=held in the audit trail. Holds win
# over --only.
#
# UPDATER_HOLD_PACKAGES="linux-image-* nvidia-* docker-ce"

# ── Security-only filtering ───────────────────────────────────────────
# When yes, restricts upgrades to security-flagged packages. Filtered-out
# packages are reported with status=filtered_non_security.
#
# UPDATER_SECURITY_ONLY=no

# ── Maintenance window ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HH:MM-HH:MM (24-hour, local time). When set, --apply outside the window
# exits 6 with status=out_of_window. --dry-run ignores the window. Use
# --force to override.
#
# UPDATER_MAINTENANCE_WINDOW=02:00-04:00

# ── Snapshot requirement (v0: stubbed) ────────────────────────────────
# When yes, --apply refuses to run unless a snapshot exists. v0 ships a
# stub that always reports missing; setting this to yes will exit 2
# (status=snapshot_missing) until real snapshot integration lands.
#
# UPDATER_REQUIRE_SNAPSHOT=no

# ── Reboot policy (v0: action stubbed) ────────────────────────────────
# One of: never (default), if-required. v0 records the post-update reboot
# signal as status=reboot_required but does NOT auto-reboot regardless
# of policy. The action ships in v0.2.
#
# UPDATER_REBOOT_POLICY=never
